.TH MPF-GUI 1 "June 2026" "MPF" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mpf-gui \- Avalonia desktop frontend for the MPF disc-dumping workflow
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mpf-gui
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mpf-gui
(upstream \fBMPF.Avalonia\fR) is the desktop GUI of the Media
Preservation Frontend (MPF) suite. It drives a complete dump session
graphically: pick a backend dumper, configure metadata, watch progress
and review the generated submission info \(em all without leaving the
window.

Supported backend dumpers:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR redumper (1)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR aaru (1)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR discimagecreator (1)
.RE
.PP
The companion validator
.BR mpf-check (1)
is invoked automatically at the end of a session to produce
\fI!submissionInfo.txt\fR.

A
.I mpf-gui.desktop
launcher is installed at
.IR /usr/share/applications/ ,
so the program can also be started from the desktop application menu.
.SH WAYLAND
Avalonia 11.x ships only an X11 backend (Avalonia.X11) \(em there is
no native Wayland backend yet. On Wayland sessions
.B mpf-gui
therefore runs through
.BR Xwayland .
Fedora Workstation and KDE Plasma install
.B xorg-x11-server-Xwayland
by default, so no extra setup is normally required. On X11 sessions
the program runs natively.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B mpf-gui
loads its configuration from
.IR config.json :
.RS
.IP 1. 3
.I ./config.json
(next to the binary or in the current working directory)
.IP 2. 3
.I ~/.config/mpf/config.json
.RE
.PP
On Fedora the second location is the canonical place to put your
config since the installed binary path is not user-writable.
.SH SYSTEM-INSTALLED DUMPERS
Unlike the upstream zip, the Fedora package does
.B not
ship a bundled \fIPrograms/Creator/\fR folder. The system-installed
.BR redumper (1),
.BR aaru (1)
and
.BR discimagecreator (1)
are resolved via
.BR PATH :
.PP
.RS
.B sudo dnf install redumper aaru discimagecreator
.RE
.SH DRIVE ACCESS
.B CAP_SYS_RAWIO
is preset on the shipped binary so vendor SCSI commands work without
sudo. Drive-node access on
.I /dev/sr*
is granted automatically via
.B uaccess
at a local desktop seat; for headless/SSH add yourself to the
.B cdrom
group:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo usermod -aG cdrom $USER
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib64/mpf-gui/MPF.Avalonia
The actual self-contained .NET binary (cap_sys_rawio=ep).
.TP
.I /usr/bin/mpf-gui
Shell wrapper that exec\(aqs the binary above.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/mpf-gui.desktop
Desktop launcher (Exec=mpf-gui, Icon=mpf).
.TP
.I ~/.config/mpf/config.json
User configuration.
.SH NOTES
This manpage is handwritten and tracks upstream MPF
.BR 3.7.1 .
If the upstream tool grows new flags or changes its syntax in a future
release, this page may lag behind the binary; consult
\fImpf-gui --help\fR for the authoritative current option set.
